{
  "texts": [
    "Similarly, mistakes of API, such as API mis-migration or misuse, are still typically due to the unfamiliarity of both PLs when translation.",
    "In summary, we attribute failures concerning Logic to the lack of comprehension of the source program (38.51%).",
    "Besides, we argue the I/O failure is induced by missing explicit I/O type declaration (14.94%).",
    "Finally, we credit mistakes relevant to Syntax, API, and Precision to the ignorance of the discrepancies between source and target PLs (41.38%).Enlightened by the above findings in the manual analysis, we carry an idea of introducing test cases as extra information to alleviate the limitations of LLMs during their code translation, and the reasons are three-fold.",
    "Firstly, test cases imply the requirements of programs, facilitating LLMs' comprehension of the program logic."
  ]
}